violations.message: The HERE project Maven:com.here.platform.examples:olp-rest-apis:1.0.8-SNAPSHOT has a dependency licensed under the strong copyleft license GPL-2.0-only which is not allowed, see http://s.here.com/FqrW2g for details. The license was declared in the package Maven:org.checkerframework:checker-compat-qual:2.0.0. For help with resolving this violation, see http://s.here.com/z3fjOk.
violations.how_to_fix:
It may be possible to resolve this violation using a curation that concludes the license(s) or 
sets the correct source code location to scan.

1. Use Git to clone [oss/tools/review-toolkit/configuration](https://gerrit.it.here.com/#/admin/projects/oss/tools/review-toolkit/configuration).
2. Open the file `curations.yml` in a text editor.
3. The comment at the top of this file describes the YAML structure for a curation.
4. Review the scan results to find the lines where the violations in Maven:org.checkerframework:checker-compat-qual:2.0.0 were flagged, then:

    - Download the scan results via `compressed HTML files` link in the OSSREVIEW ticket, or ...
    - Expand 'Package Scan Results' in the Web App scan report.

5. Open https://github.com/typetools/checker-framework.git in a web browser and find the code for the version shown in the Maven:org.checkerframework:checker-compat-qual:2.0.0.

    6. If this package is part of a repository containing multiple Maven packages, then add an entry for Maven:org.checkerframework:checker-compat-qual:2.0.0 
       in `curations.yml` setting `path` under `vcs` to the repository directory that contains the source code for the package.
       Continue to step 9 below.

       Examples:
       - [Gerrit change 1124906](https://gerrit.it.here.com/#/c/1124906/)
    7. Download and extract the [binary artifact](https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/checkerframework/checker-compat-qual/2.0.0/checker-compat-qual-2.0.0.jar) (`.jar`) for Maven:org.checkerframework:checker-compat-qual:2.0.0.
    8. Determine the applicable licenses for the `.jar` by comparing its contents with the scan results.
       If you cannot find a file with the specific license from the scan results in the `tar.gz` then consider the license as non-applicable.
       For the licenses that do apply to the `.jar`, create an entry for Maven:org.checkerframework:checker-compat-qual:2.0.0 in `curations.yml` with `concluded_license` 
       containing [SPDX license expression](https://spdx.github.io/spdx-spec/appendix-IV-SPDX-license-expressions/).

       Examples:
       - [Gerrit change 1133155](https://gerrit.it.here.com/#/c/1133155/)
       - [Gerrit change 1144632](https://gerrit.it.here.com/#/c/1144632/)
    9. Submit your Gerrit change, reviewers are set automatically.
    

Note: Do not worry about creating a perfect curation. All curations are reviewed by the Open Source Office so you will get feedback.

Related docs:
[Resolving Rule Violations](https://confluence.in.here.com/display/OSS/Resolving+Rule+Violations)

violations.how_to_fix:
This violation can be resolved using the steps below:

1. Using an editor of your choice update each pom.xml in 
2. Add <LICENSES> as shown in below example.
```

<licenses>
    <!-- Include only licenses found in repository and not its dependencies -->
    <license>
        <name>HERE Proprietary License</name>
        <url>https://here.com</url>
        <distribution>repo</distribution>
        <comments>SPDX-License-Identifier: LicenseRef-Proprietary-HERE</comments>
    </license>
</licenses>
```
